'''Denys Gueroult''' [[Order of the British Empire|MBE]] ([[25 September]] [[1927]]<ref>{{webcite|website=[http://www.findthecompany.co.uk/ FindTheCompany]|articleurl=http://directors.findthecompany.co.uk/l/280720/Denys-Gueroult|articlename=Denys Gueroult - Director Profile|accessed=16 December 2014}}</ref> - [[29 July]] [[2014]]<ref>{{webcite|website=[https://www.thegazette.co.uk/ The Gazette]|articleurl=https://www.thegazette.co.uk/notice/2200711|articlename=Denys Gueroult - Deceased Estates|accessed=16 December 2014}}</ref>) was a [[BBC]] producer responsible for a [[Index:Audio recordings of J.R.R. Tolkien|recorded interview]] with [[J.R.R. Tolkien]] in [[January]] [[1965]], known as ''[[An Interview with J.R.R.T.]]''

"Denys Gueroult" is the spelling used in ''[[The J.R.R. Tolkien Companion and Guide]]'' and [[Minas Tirith Evening-Star (Volume 8, Number 2)|''Minas Tirith Evening-Star'' (Volume 8, Number 2)]]. Variant spellings in different works are: Denis, Dennis, Denys, David, Gueroult, Gerrolt, Gerroult. In the archives of the [[Marquette University]], the name is spelt "Denis Guerouit".<ref>[http://www.marquette.edu/library/collections/archives/Mss/JRRT/mss-jrrt-s-5.html Ephemera, Collectibles, Audio Visual Material: Secondary Material relation to Tolkien, 1938-]</ref>
